entry.tran: (橄榄球中的)攻方持球越线得分，达阵
entry.def: In rugby and American football, a touchdown is when a team scores points by taking the ball over the opposition's goal line.

means.word_mean: 1. a score in American football; being in possession of the ball across the opponents' goal line
2. a landing (as the wheels touch the landing field); especially of airplanes
